title: Mass spectrometric determination of Rb fission yields from 3He and 4He induced fission of 238U and 232Th

x4freetext: Mass spectrometric determination of Rb fission yields
from 3He and 4He induced fission of 238U and 232Th

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Chemistry, Vol.61, p.786 (1983)

x4codes.hlp: Pacific Northwest Laboratories, Richland, WA, United States of America
Washington University, St.Louis, MO, United States of America

x4freetext: 54-in sector-focused cyclotron at
Washington University, St. Louis.
At 32-MeV, a 3He beam intensity of I microA gave a
typical 91Rb counting rate of about I5,000 ions/s.
The target consisted of 238U or 232Th powder (10
microm size) intimately mixed with graphite powder
and pressed into a small block about 100 mg/cm2
thick. The ratio of metal-to-graphite was 4-to-1 by
weight.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Uncertainties are based only on the
standard deviation of the mean values. Values with no
uncertainty were used to normalize different runs.
The correction factor for growth, decay, and
diffusion was implemented. The saturation factor
corrected for those isotopes whose half-lives were an
appreciable fraction of the total run time. The
maximum corrections were 40% for mass 89 and 2% for
mass 90 for a run with 34 MeV 3He on a 238U target.
The correction for radioactive decay requires
knowledge of the diffusion components.
BP
The relative cumulative yields of Rb isotopes
were measured by scanning the mass spectrum rapidly
while the cyclotron beam was on continuously. The
mass spectrum was scanned by holding the magnetic
field constant and imposing a triangular waveform to
the accelerating voltage at a repetition rate of 25
cycles/s. Sweep up and sweep down mass spectra were
stored separately in 100 channel segments of a
multiscaler.
Table 2, page 788.

x4freetext: The measurement of Rb independent yields must
be done in a time interval short compared to the
radioactive half-lives of the Kr precursors. Thus a
pulsed beam procedure was used in which mass spectra
were recorded with "beam-on" for a short time
interval and were separately recorded with "beam-off"
for the same time interval.
Table 3, page 790.
